IGA’s market share has fallen from 18 percent to 14 percent since 2010, and revenue from Metcash’s food and grocery trade, which supplies about 1,200 IGA retailers, has fallen by 43 percent since 2012, reflecting operational debt relief while putting pressure on revenue and margins.
